<exercise id="fs-id2399594" type="ap-test-prep"><problem id="fs-id1742414">
<para id="fs-id1467442">In an experiment a negatively charged balloon (balloon X) is repelled by another charged balloon Y. However, an object Z is attracted to balloon Y. Which of the following can be the charge on Z? Select <emphasis effect="italics">two</emphasis> answers.</para>
