      <glossary>
     <definition id="fs-id1169762564340"><term>electric charge</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169762326627">a physical property of an object that causes it to be attracted toward or repelled from another charged object; each charged object generates and is influenced by a force called an electromagnetic force</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169762531365"><term>law of conservation of charge</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169762340305">states that whenever a charge is created, an equal amount of charge with the opposite sign is created simultaneously</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169762618707"><term>electron</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169760252428">a particle orbiting the nucleus of an atom and carrying the smallest unit of negative charge</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169762363094"><term>proton</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169762652687">a particle in the nucleus of an atom and carrying a positive charge equal in magnitude and opposite in sign to the amount of negative charge carried by an electron</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
